{"name": "filedialpy", "metadata": {"name": "filedialpy", "version": "1.3.0", "classifiers": ["Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Package for opening native file dialogs on linux, macOS and windows.", "upload_time": 1732521872}, "documentation": ["# filedialpy\n\nPython package for opening native file dialogs on linux, macOS and windows. It uses either zenity or kdialog on linux, pywin32 on windows and applescript on macOS.\n\n## Installation\n\n```\npip install filedialpy\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```\nimport filedialpy\n\nf=filedialpy.openFile()    # Open a single file (return a string)\nf=filedialpy.openFiles()   # Open multiple files (return a list of strings)\nf=filedialpy.openDir()     # Open a directory (return a string)\nf=filedialpy.saveFile()    # Save to a new file (return a string)\n\n# Using additional options\nf=filedialpy.saveFile(initial_dir=\"/home/user/Documents\",initial_file=\"config.json\",title=\"Save config file\", filter=[\"*.json\",\"*\"])\n```\n\n## Options\n\n- **initial_dir**: Initial directory where to start the search (current working directory if not specified).\n- **initial_file**: Initial filename.\n- **title**: Title for the dialog window.\n- **filter**: string \"*.json *.txt\" (different accepted extensions can be separated by a space), or a list of such strings in order to provide several possible filters.\n\n\n## Acknowledgements\nThe implementation of filedialpy was inspired by [crossfiledialog](https://github.com/maikelwever/crossfiledialog).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "filedialpy.linux_tkinter", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "filedialpy.linux_tkinter.convert_filter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filter", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "filedialpy.linux_tkinter.openFile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "initial_dir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "initial_file", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "filter", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "title", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "filedialpy.linux_tkinter.openFiles", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "initial_dir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "initial_file", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "filter", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "title", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "filedialpy.linux_tkinter.openDir", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "initial_dir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "initial_file", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "filter", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "title", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "filedialpy.linux_tkinter.saveFile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "initial_dir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "initial_file", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "filter", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "title", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "confirm_overwrite", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "filedialpy.linux_kdialog", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "filedialpy.linux_kdialog.kdialog_wrapper", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "initial_dir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "initial_file", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "filter", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "title", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "multiple", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "directory", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "save", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "filedialpy.linux_kdialog.openFile", "asynchrono